  Locus:
    Page: 482
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - War
---
Truth that has merely been learned is like an artificial limb, a false
tooth, a waxen nose, it adheres to us only because it is put on. But truth
acquired by thought of our own is like a natural limb, it alone belongs to
us.
